main event: Two observers reported seeing two bright objects pass overhead at high speed on December 30, 1959 near Centerville, Ohio.
interesting points: The observers were watching television in a private home when they observed the two bright objects.
The observers were unable to determine the true nature of the sighted objects.
Additional information could not be obtained due to the lack of visual observations.
The report concludes the sighted objects were 'possibly Balloon/Aircraft' and 'Was Not an Unknown'.
The observer called the Air Force on March 8, 1959 to report seeing a very bright light in the northwest sky that suddenly split into two lights and then faded and went out, lasting about 1 minute.
witnesses: two observers in a private home
